commit_message:
Fixes incorrect processing of deleting metadata

When a non-admin tries to delete metadata from a marked image,
they are correctly getting an error message, however they are
also getting a success message when they shouldn't. This code
fixes the incorrect success message.

Closes-Bug: #1308519
Change-Id: I909551365b4a92675d26c1da754e586685a4aa32

commit_message:
ssh instance validation add options for Neutron

This is the first part of the patch series which
 implements multiple ssh instance validation strategy.

This patch adds the new config options and have the effected
test classes to prepare the basic neutron resources for usage.

The default is using the fixed ips for connection, but
on the devstack side the configuration options are configured,
for neutron usage.

Change-Id: Ic5fc9bd1f7407d3430fcd33b03a226deed696d57
Implements: blueprint ssh-auth-strategy

commit_message:
Make instance_exists() take an instance, not instance_name

Some virt drivers may not support/need to use instance.name and have
a different way to find out if an instance exists. NOTE: this still
uses dict access on instance, as the _run_instance() path is not
converted to Instance objects yet.

NOTE: This also removes a duplicate call to self._lookup_by_name()
in libvirt's resume_state_on_host_boot(). It was calling
self.instance_exists() and then self._lookup_by_name(), but instance_exists()
calls _lookup_by_name() itself.

Change-Id: I701cb5416ec47262268d1a088018b6be2774d1c5

commit_message:
Fix H302 violations in extensions package

H302 violation is reported by flake8 when importing separated objects from
modules instead of importing the whole module.
e.g.   from package.module import function
       function()
is changed to
       from package import module
       module.function()

Change-Id: I570eeee2a7633c1590b54ac98b411a71fc9d4f4e
Partial-Bug: #1291032

subject: fix test_compute_with_volumes
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 2750, 'name': 'Sean Dague', 'email': 'sean@dague.net', 'username': 'sdague'}, {'_account_id': 5196, 'name': 'Matthew Treinish', 'email': 'mtreinish@kortar.org', 'username': 'treinish'}, {'_account_id': 5803, 'name': 'Attila Fazekas', 'email': 'afazekas@redhat.com', 'username': 'afazekas'}, {'_account_id': 7872, 'name': 'Marc Koderer', 'email': 'marc@koderer.com', 'username': 'mkoderer'}, {'_account_id': 10385, 'name': 'Citrix XenServer CI', 'username': 'citrix_xenserver_ci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2014-04-23 15:46:07.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/thirdparty/boto/test_ec2_instance_run.py'], 'message': "fix test_compute_with_volumes

The test_integration_1 test was waiting on volume being in an
'in-use' state before proceeding. However the 'in-use' state
doesn't actually mean that the volume is attached, as 'attaching'
gets mapped to 'in-use' in nova.

This makes it possible for the test to proceed when the volume is
in an attaching state, and not actually ever attached. Which means
you can get to the detach phase on an non attached volume, and
thus explode.

Use the attachment status to filter out when then volume is not
actually ready.

In the process, make the test name something that's actually
descriptive for what it does.

Related-Bug: #1302774

Change-Id: Iaeb6a42a39b4adf8cb4bdff64efe00bf14821725
"}]
commit_message:
fix test_compute_with_volumes

The test_integration_1 test was waiting on volume being in an
'in-use' state before proceeding. However the 'in-use' state
doesn't actually mean that the volume is attached, as 'attaching'
gets mapped to 'in-use' in nova.

This makes it possible for the test to proceed when the volume is
in an attaching state, and not actually ever attached. Which means
you can get to the detach phase on an non attached volume, and
thus explode.

Use the attachment status to filter out when then volume is not
actually ready.

In the process, make the test name something that's actually
descriptive for what it does.

Related-Bug: #1302774

Change-Id: Iaeb6a42a39b4adf8cb4bdff64efe00bf14821725

commit_message:
correcting the elements sequence for centos+hdp+plain+debug

When creating a centos image with the hdp plain plugin and with debug
mode on the root password is not set correctly. This change fixes the
element sequence.

Changes
* renaming the elements sequence variable for centos hdp plain images

Change-Id: I9e6a46c64cf6239fd6635c2e5673b258a0c4a6fd

commit_message:
Enable keystone token auth and ec2 auth

This patch enables keystone token auth and ec2 auth. Also it enables
keystone support in tempest.

Also, magnetodb section was added to tempest config.

Change-Id: I3e20ab7c66350cbb4a02c5401c43502b3cbaa461
Implements: blueprint keystone-token-validation

commit_message:
Verify addrs only against ports with fixed IPs

To verify a port's mac and IP address, the list of neutron ports is
used. We cannot check against ports without fixed IP addresses, so
exclude them.

Change-Id: Ib81ab42cdbae3132af735b0020ca59d22b71ebaf
Closes-bug: #1300322

We need to ensure that tokens won't stay in cache after they have been
revoked.

Changed default revocation_cache_time 300 -> 10 seconds.
revocation_cache_time has to be << than token_cache_time to make token

commit_message:
Ensure that cached token is not revoked

We need to ensure that tokens won't stay in cache after they have been
revoked.

Changed default revocation_cache_time 300 -> 10 seconds.
revocation_cache_time has to be << than token_cache_time to make token
cache efficient.

Fixes bug #1287301

Change-Id: I14c0eacac3b431c06e40385c891a6636736e5b4a

commit_message:
safe_setup preserve original trace

When safe_setup reraies the exception the traceback was
replaced by the trace of the re-raise postion.

This change is aiming to preserve the original stack trace,
by saving the original trace and raiseing new exception from the same
type with the original trace.

Change-Id: I16851a0c1d40d7f7253c23f066fa8c19267f4d9a

calls it's done against neutron it should pass device_id='' instead of
None otherwise neutron raises an exception.

Note: This should have a unit test but it's near impossible
to add one right without duplicating all of _stub_allocate_for_instance
due to the fact that it's using some crazy logic in the tests to make
decisions based on an index that's passed it. X.x

Change-Id: I91334c07401ff379f71fdef1d5bd080cc68a72ab
Closes-bug: #1285886
"}]
commit_message:
Nova should pass device_id='' instead of None to neutron.update_port()

In the case that neutron raises an error and nova needs to undo the api
calls it's done against neutron it should pass device_id='' instead of
None otherwise neutron raises an exception.

Note: This should have a unit test but it's near impossible
to add one right without duplicating all of _stub_allocate_for_instance
due to the fact that it's using some crazy logic in the tests to make
decisions based on an index that's passed it. X.x

Change-Id: I91334c07401ff379f71fdef1d5bd080cc68a72ab
Closes-bug: #1285886

commit_message:
Fix broken retry tests

* Failure was in output transformer specified in retry_task.yaml.
* Added assertion back to enable the tests.
* Extra logging to include more context in the logs to gather more insight from the logs.

Change-Id: Ic6f4665cd4d74d2676fc17891dbf66984926cd42

commit_message:
Limited use trusts

Trusts now have a "remaining_uses" field that tracks how many times
a trust can still issue a token. It is decremented by 1 each time a
trust related authentication occurs (call to /auth/tokens), until it
reaches 0 and no token can be issued through this trust anymore. If
set to null (default value), trusts can be used indefinitely to
authenticate.
This is the client side of the implementation.

Closes-Bug: #1250617
Implements: bp trusts-chained-delegation

Change-Id: Ib035a9772b7f035c3a9af102e8e15a860a96a96d

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-03-04 17:33:03.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/exceptions.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/volumes/volumes/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/templates/exceptions/novaclient/OverLimit.html', 'openstack_dashboard/templates/exceptions/default.html', 'openstack_dashboard/templates/exceptions/base.html', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/containers/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/templates/exceptions/neutronclient/NeutronClientException.html'], 'message': 'Better error message handling

In OpenStack dashboard, error messages that pop up to end users
present several problems:
 * When they are based on exception message,
   they are often too technical and/or not helpful.
 * When they are set by horizon code, they cannot
   (without changing source code) be customized by cloud
   providers (that may want to adapt them to their business rules)

This patch is a first attempt to address this problem.
It's a work in progress and we hope it will be a good
start for discussions and early feedbacks.

How does it work:
 * It adds an adapter class called HTMLException:
   it's aimed to be the HTML part of an exception.
   HTMLException wrap python exceptions when it happen and provides a
   method called "render" that knows how to render
   the underlying exception object.

 * When an exception is being rendered, the render method will
   look up for a django templates (for that, it tries to map
   the exception class name to a template name),
   if no specific template for that class of exception in defined,
   it falls back to a default template.

 * Templates are created under a directory called "exceptions",
   "base" and "default" template can be provided by OpenStack dashboard,
   when specific exceptions templates may be defined by users
   throw another Django application. (we include specific template
   in this patch mainly for example).

 * To be flexible on how to render an exception,
   templates will get in their context:
     * The exception object being raised
     * The exception class
     * The exception traceback.
     * Error message set in horizon source code (if any).

Partially implements: blueprint improve-error-message-details-for-usability

Change-Id: If634c684769f1b865d35568cb2e9747108f0012a
'}]
commit_message:
Better error message handling

In OpenStack dashboard, error messages that pop up to end users
present several problems:
 * When they are based on exception message,
   they are often too technical and/or not helpful.
 * When they are set by horizon code, they cannot
   (without changing source code) be customized by cloud
   providers (that may want to adapt them to their business rules)

This patch is a first attempt to address this problem.
It's a work in progress and we hope it will be a good
start for discussions and early feedbacks.

How does it work:
 * It adds an adapter class called HTMLException:
   it's aimed to be the HTML part of an exception.
   HTMLException wrap python exceptions when it happen and provides a
   method called "render" that knows how to render
   the underlying exception object.

 * When an exception is being rendered, the render method will
   look up for a django templates (for that, it tries to map
   the exception class name to a template name),
   if no specific template for that class of exception in defined,
   it falls back to a default template.

 * Templates are created under a directory called "exceptions",
   "base" and "default" template can be provided by OpenStack dashboard,
   when specific exceptions templates may be defined by users
   throw another Django application. (we include specific template
   in this patch mainly for example).

 * To be flexible on how to render an exception,
   templates will get in their context:
     * The exception object being raised
     * The exception class
     * The exception traceback.
     * Error message set in horizon source code (if any).

Partially implements: blueprint improve-error-message-details-for-usability

Change-Id: If634c684769f1b865d35568cb2e9747108f0012a

Added help button for modal forms

*** Help button has the same size/look as the quit button

*** We are currently changing the look n feel of the modal
    forms since we are loosing a great portion of the page for the
    help text which is not always required (also prevent us from making
    the layout horizon). So, we are making the help text toggable.

    All other modals are the same for now.

commit_message:
Define nova enabled_apis as Heat-configurable

This change is to define the nova enabled_apis option configurable via Heat.
At the moment this option is hard coded in the nova.conf, here we define
this parameter in the yaml template for the undercloud and overcloud.
For the overcloud the parameter is defined just for the notcompute nodes.

The parameter has a default value which is equals to the value we currently
set in the nova element.
The next step will be to change the nova element to get the value from Heat.

Change-Id: Ib7094a39df6a367f3a0ac80b3e417576335a4837

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-20 05:32:21.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/agent/linux/interface.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/test_linux_interface.py'], 'message': 'Fix unshortened IPv6 address caused DHCP crash

When unshortened IPv6 address provided to allocation pool, DHCP
agent crashed because OpenStack is trying to add same IPv6 addresses
to dhcp tap device.

The root cause is that current code compares provided unshortened
IPv6 address with the returned result of "ip addr list", which is
shortened. So the same IPv6 address is treated as different ones.

The fix is trying to shorten the provided address before comparison.

Change-Id: If1e183e65c5ab785b73771d9a3d4b525d38284a9
Closes-Bug: 1266780
'}]
commit_message:
Fix unshortened IPv6 address caused DHCP crash

When unshortened IPv6 address provided to allocation pool, DHCP
agent crashed because OpenStack is trying to add same IPv6 addresses
to dhcp tap device.

The root cause is that current code compares provided unshortened
IPv6 address with the returned result of "ip addr list", which is
shortened. So the same IPv6 address is treated as different ones.

The fix is trying to shorten the provided address before comparison.

Change-Id: If1e183e65c5ab785b73771d9a3d4b525d38284a9
Closes-Bug: 1266780

commit_message:
Add set-pip-vars script to simplify pip manifests

Adding a scripts/set-pip-vars script that simplifies the setting
of DIB_PIP_MANIFEST_ environment variables from pip manifests for
disk image builds

Intent is that developers can run e.g. :

 source <(set-pip-vars ${TRIPLEO_ROOT}/undercloud_manifest)

To set all their DIB_PIP_MANIFEST environment variables for
building that stack of tripleo.

e.g. deploy-ramdisk, seed, undercloud, overcloud-control, overcloud-compute

In addition that they can use it to alter their setup:

e.g. source <(set-pip-vars my-manifest/dib-pip-manifest*client)

Change-Id: Ibdd9a0e928bcea87f024a8e980bcc816ff1fd0a6

The oslo.messaging library is expecting a property called transport_url

commit_message:
Fix incorrect transport property

The oslo.messaging library is expecting a property called transport_url
not transport_host. Because we are setting the notifier_strategy to
'default' without a valid transport oslo.messging does not know which MQ
driver to instantiate and it can instantiate Rabbit's even though the MQ
type might be QPID.

Change-Id: Ib29aee1ce06712c43a457dfe8c9a3efdce5a8f33
Closes-Bug: #1311823

subject: Don't explode if we fail to unplug VIFs after a failed boot
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-04-22 17:25:55.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/virt/libvirt/test_libvirt.py', 'nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py'], 'message': "Don't explode if we fail to unplug VIFs after a failed boot

Libvirt currently attempts to unplug VIFs after destroying an
instance, which can fail if the instance was never built
properly in the first place. This patch makes it ignore errors
when trying to tear down VIFs during that cleanup. Failure
in this case would block the deletion of the instance (which
should never happen) and any real failures aren't something
we could do anything about.

Closes-bug: #1306718

Change-Id: I84a4433c3959b8f14e0259be0aa51da1654006c8
(cherry picked from commit b3225581befe14f21b909e176d0a4583b297e031)
"}]
commit_message:
Don't explode if we fail to unplug VIFs after a failed boot

Libvirt currently attempts to unplug VIFs after destroying an
instance, which can fail if the instance was never built
properly in the first place. This patch makes it ignore errors
when trying to tear down VIFs during that cleanup. Failure
in this case would block the deletion of the instance (which
should never happen) and any real failures aren't something
we could do anything about.

Closes-bug: #1306718

Change-Id: I84a4433c3959b8f14e0259be0aa51da1654006c8

commit_message:
NSX: Fix fake_api_client to raise NotFound

If one quries NSX doing GET /ws.v1/lswitch/LS_UUID/lport and LS_UUID
is a UUID that does not exist in NSX. NSX raises a 404. If LS_UUID is *
NSX returns an empty result string. This patch fixes the fake_api_client
so that it's behavior is correct.

Change-Id: Id66299d6ae3cfa43a65d4cb28f34348d64d8ed65
Closes-bug: 1311291
(cherry picked from commit dd143a619900792a0563b9ac4fe1f78197291d94)

commit_message:
gw_port should be set as lazy='join'

This forces the object to be ready ahead of accessing time.
The change in loading behavior is also beneficial while listing
routers, as reduces the amount of queries being issued. Tests
show a performance gain of 15-30% for router-list times.

As Mr. Aaron Rosen is used to saying: Woot woot!!

Closes-bug: #1309144

Change-Id: Ibae261b91de26ca7c50e3f6c80e9be2a799785a3
(cherry picked from commit 966dbb5368d710e2652b18f5b9cb4295f58598da)

commit_message:
Ignore InstanceNotFound while getting console output

During we cold-migrating or resizing an instance to another host,
or during deleting it, the get_console_output method may raise an
InstanceNotFound excetpion if the instance is not on the hypervisor,
this is an expected error, so we should add it to expected
exceptions list in compute manager.

Closes-bug: #1292339
Change-Id: I23a99438d73826f01ff5662130dcbfa72dc39a6e

commit_message:
Fix the catalog format of a sample token

This token is used for auth_token testing and is a valid v3 token other
than the catalog which is in v2 format.

Convert the catalog to V3 format. Whilst there pretty print the token so
we can more easily see what's happening.

Change-Id: I893ea6e76f3fcc20b13b331911d7b8288b98991d

commit_message:
Add new error for invalid response

There are a number of places where we expect a certain format of
response. If it's not found we often end up raising a KeyError when
accessing data.

Create a new Exception type that is raised when a HTTP response is not
appropriate for parsing and use it within authentication calls.

Closes-Bug: #1307306
Change-Id: I3cf2db07a8e76ee17702130e9efb0edf640d293a

commit_message:
Added mounting and umounting /target

It turned out that in some cases it is necessary to umount
all mount points which are connected to a particular disk
before creating other partitions on that disk.

Change-Id: I43a2de132415d026a6dc096e2b25ce0ab4cce915
Closes-Bug: #1297792

commit_message:
Fix up StringIO use in tests for py3

Some spots in this file were already referencing six.StringIO, but
some were still using StringIO.StringIO, which does not work on
py3. This patch just makes them all use six.StringIO and removes the
now-unused (and wrong, on py3) import.

Change-Id: I3c7311c3983f4eb409eedb6f85ede6ffe4059e63

commit_message:
Verify flavor extra specs attributes of Nova APIs

This patch adds the JSON schema for Nova V2/V3 flavor extra specs APIs
response and validate the response with added JSON schema to
block the backward incompatibility change in the future.

The response body of flavor extra specs APIs are below:

Response of set & get extra specs of V2 & V3-

{
    "extra_specs": {
        "key1": "%(value1)s",
        "key2": "%(value2)s"
    }
}
Response code of set extra specs API differ-
 200 - V2
 201 - V3

Response of update & get extra specs key of V2 & V3-

{
    "key1": "%(value1)s"
}

Response code of unset extra specs API differ-
 200 - V2
 204 - V3
This does not return any response body.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I41e566cb484d0b7fa29197c639f9f231c8c32ea9

commit_message:
Cannot enable namespace deletion in L3/DHCP agents

Currently devstack can be configure L3 and DHCP agents
to use namespaces using the Q_USE_NAMESPACE option.
However, it cannot enable namespace deletion. This patch
creates a Q_DELETE_NAMESPACE option that can configure
DHCP and L3 agents with the namespace deletion enabled.

Change-Id: Id83db89b7daeac5424b8fbb4271bed42eb390d86
Closes-bug: 1299321

commit_message:
Improve combination rule validation

Combination rule alarms should contain at least two different alarms
in the alarm_ids list. This patch adds a check to the validate method
of AlarmCombinationRule and raise ClientSideError, if the condition
fails.

Closes-Bug: #1305519

Change-Id: Ic5968d6ecf5781070cab39274131e605619e264a

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-04-17 12:58:51.000000000', 'files': ['swift/common/middleware/list_endpoints.py', 'test/unit/common/middleware/test_list_endpoints.py'], 'message': "Quick fix to Storage Policy Support for List Endpoints

The path being sent to get_container_info didn't include the ver
so downstream path parsers were off by one on interpretting
parms.  get_info is mocked in unit tests so not caught there,
found while doing an example for the docs.  The version doesn't

functions get the parms correct.

Implements: blueprint storage-policies
"}]
commit_message:
Quick fix to Storage Policy Support for List Endpoints

The path being sent to get_container_info didn't include the ver
so downstream path parsers were off by one on interpretting
parms.  get_info is mocked in unit tests so not caught there,
found while doing an example for the docs.  The version doesn't
matter in this case, just need a placeholder so the downstream
functions get the parms correct.

Also added policy support for custom endpoint names which was
missing before and tightened up unit test coverage for both
functional issues addressed here.

Change-Id: I56d4b0f4f321a4c72b11ec44d868a194d02ea3a3
Implements: blueprint storage-policies

commit_message:
NSX: Fix fake_api_client to raise NotFound

If one quries NSX doing GET /ws.v1/lswitch/LS_UUID/lport and LS_UUID
is a UUID that does not exist in NSX. NSX raises a 404. If LS_UUID is *
NSX returns an empty result string. This patch fixes the fake_api_client
so that it's behavior is correct.

Change-Id: Id66299d6ae3cfa43a65d4cb28f34348d64d8ed65
Closes-bug: 1311291

commit_message:
Make endpoint commands more consistent

Make endpoints more consistent across create, show, etc
* Make the name option required for create
* Use a common function to fetch services by id, name or type
* Have show work by endpoint id or by service id, type or name
* Have show display all the fields by default
* Remove capability to filter queries by attribute value pairs

Change-Id: Idaa4b8d930ba859fd62de777e44a10b1ed58c79b
Partial-Bug: #1184012

commit_message:
Fix the project option to user list so it filters

The --project option to the user list command was not implemented
* Allow users to be filted by project
* Support id or name of project with the find_resource command
* Make sure the report does not contain duplicates

Closes-Bug: #1177255

commit_message:
Decrement rules_index for duplicate chains

Decrement rules_index if we encounter a duplicate chain (a chain
that neutron wants to create that already exists) to avoid
inserting the ruleset at the wrong point which can cause
iptables-restore to fail and in turn vif plugging to also fail.

Closes-Bug: 1311904
Change-Id: I9d88a4a8195f9f4a03bb8ba2accf2b9febeff42d

commit_message:
Add "daemon" flag to marconi script

This patch adds daemon flag to marconi script. This change was
needed to run the latest build of marconi-server in background.
Since mongodb can not be used with marconi until gate is updated
to Ubuntu 14.04, we are changing our backend to sqlite.

Change-Id: I1a4148bd545818d5e943257be2f6e752ce43f793

commit_message:
Allow get_nodeinfo_list to filter provision_state

This allows you to pass a state or list of states to get_nodeinfo_list()
as a filter to only return Nodes with matching provision_states.

This is used in a follow up patch to re-factor conductor's
_check_deploy_timeouts() periodic task.

Change-Id: Iaf0dc1d08dcc472a4b15ad0d2b1e4a5249e07331

commit_message:
ML2 conf options for openvswitch and linuxbridge

When using ML2, the mechanism drivers (openvswitch, linuxbridge) need
some attributes defined in the ml2_conf.ini configuration file.
This change simply makes the existing openvswitch and linuxbridge
attributes available within the ml2_conf.ini file in the proper sections.

Change-Id: I10f1b2c9aae08150f2b0667b62a905f92de5daad
Closes-Bug: #1311311

commit_message:
Add basic reporting to engine

This patch adds reporting system to engine.
It is used in two major places
a) to report error to API when exception occurs
b) report service status reports to API via workflow as
- $this.find(std:Environment).reporter.report($this, 'Creating VM.')

Change-Id: I7310931482447e174114164ed921bb3fcbfb9d66

commit_message:
xenapi: make auto_config_disk persist boot flag

Currently auto_config_disk creates a new partition that ignores many
settings on the original partition.

The key flag that should be respected is the "boot" flag. When present
on the old partition, it should be present on the new partition.

Change-Id: I0408112cd60046422d6863651323fc9a7313d488
Closes-bug: #1265465

commit_message:
Change the way 'do_redirect' flag is passed into WizardView

This change eliminates the need to have a specific url for each
combination of optional parameters passed to WizardView, thus making
possible to pass more than optional parameter to WizardView.

commit_message:
Clean up calls to get_node()

This patch removes all direct calls to dbapi's get_node(). They are
replaced either by Node.get(), Node.get_by_id(), or Node.get_by_uuid()
calls.

Additional detail about the changes:

1) Break DBAPI get_node() into get_node_by_id() and get_node_by_uuid().
   Let's be explicit about which type we're passing. This allows
   Node.get_by_uuid() to work exactly how its named. Also, do not
   return an object from the DB API calls. The Node object itself will
   do the conversion.
2) Adds Node.get_by_id() to compliment the current Node.get_by_uuid()
   for places you are querying by the ID.
3) Adds Node.get() so that you can still have a single method to use
   to pass either and ID or a UUID.
4) Make all of the Node.get* calls set the 'context' so that you can
   later just node.save() without passing it. Doc strings have been
   updated to clarify what 'context' is for.

Change-Id: I995891b1645056a5b15c48e37b8bcd1e299ac468

Change-Id: I9126c090d3d4cd03cb93735a2b0c54fa250eed61

commit_message:
Make innodb pool size configurable

Alows configuring of buffer pool size and decreases default
value to 100MB.

For VMs with 2G RAM is 592MB buffer too big. Then you can hit
an issue that openstack requests fail because there is not
enough memory to spawn new process or mysql server restart fails
for because it fails to allocate 592MB buffer.

Change-Id: I9126c090d3d4cd03cb93735a2b0c54fa250eed61

commit_message:
Add ha_nodes option to murano-repository

NOTE:
   This patch is intended only for 4.1 branch
   due to changes in murano repositories structure.

   This patch is required to have murano-repository HA mode working.

This patch adds support for 'ha_nodes' option of Murano Repository service. This
options should contain a string with all controller nodes and service ports.

Config example:
   ha_nodes = node-1:8084, node-2:8084, node-3:8084

Port 8084 will be listened by other controllers and any changes made will be
replicated to all other controllers.

Firewall should be opened to allow this port to be accessed by other
controllers through the management network.

The Repository service uses Keystone's auth tokens for authentificetion on other
controller nodes.

'nodes_to_node_port_list' function generates this string
from the array of controller nodes.

Based on: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/83146/3

Implements: blueprint murano-repository-ha

Change-Id: I4ff3005422e1360f57dd3f5e57a888dff6a19dd1

after ip address is started using

of an instance.

will add metadata "from_server_key": "value" to the instance metadata.

commit_message:
Configure SELinux to allow SSH to listen on $IRONIC_VM_SSH_PORT

Currently lib/ironic changes SSH listen port to 2222.
This won't work on SELinux-enabled systems, as SSH there
is restricted to port 22. This patch adds $IRONIC_VM_SSH_PORT
as appropriate port for sshd in SELinux.

Change-Id: I83f91cc2a18a187239a6154c6b6dbe25b54e2f63

commit_message:
fix(metadata): Fix inconsistent error response under v1.1

This patch modifies the v1.1 `on_put` responder to raise an
instance of falcon.HTTPError, including setting the Allow
header as required by RFC 2616.

This ensures that the structured JSON response body is
consistent with error bodies returned elsewhere in the
API.

A test was also added to cover the v1.1 implementation
of `on_put`.

Change-Id: I05e15cd3c676db8f9fc3fb7d1ba6fcd31613fc30
Partially-Implements: blueprint api-v1.1-remove-queue-metadata

commit_message:
RabbitMQ 3 support

RabbitMQ 3 do not support such big TTL which we used before.
Big TTL was need to solve problem with node time dissynchronization.
Now we use NTP to resolve this issue. That is why this value
can be reduced.

Related-Bug: #1278336
Related-Bug: #1276770
Change-Id: I0a56b88247d9839bc3282294cdb8592ed2701c3a

commit_message:
RabbitMQ 3 support

RabbitMQ 3 do not support such big TTL which we used before.
Big TTL was need to solve problem with node time dissynchronization.
Now we use NTP to resolve this issue. That is why this value
can be reduced.

Related-Bug: #1278336
Related-Bug: #1276770
Change-Id: Iee79f14929e9f1ac5e5e7dd07aee37f641d3b2a8

commit_message:
remove unneeded call to network_api on rebuild_instance

When rebuilding an instance we call the network_api and which results in
calling neutron and updating the info cache. We do not actually need to
do this as we can get the nw_info directly from the instance's info cache.

Change-Id: I2bcc2f15b1e5bb52d972098c7bc3e12f160b6feb
Closes-bug: 1294914

subject: Fix cinder option to set a volume to read-only access
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-04-23 17:21:48.000000000', 'files': ['doc/common/section_cli_cinder_read-only-volumes.xml'], 'message': 'Fix cinder option to set a volume to read-only access

Under the "Manage volume" section of the OpenStack End User Guide,
it says to use "cinder read-only-mode-update VOLUME BOOLEAN" to
set the volume to read-only. The option "read-only-mode-update" is
incorrect. It should be "readonly-mode-update". This patch corrects
the option used.

Change-Id: I863272f98a3289c6bab877a618c8f6e898800bd3
Closes-Bug: #1311283
'}]
commit_message:
Fix cinder option to set a volume to read-only access

Under the "Manage volume" section of the OpenStack End User Guide,
it says to use "cinder read-only-mode-update VOLUME BOOLEAN" to
set the volume to read-only. The option "read-only-mode-update" is
incorrect. It should be "readonly-mode-update". This patch corrects
the option used.

Change-Id: I863272f98a3289c6bab877a618c8f6e898800bd3
Closes-Bug: #1311283

commit_message:
Log Request ID Mappings

Tracking requests across multiple OpenStack services is difficult.
This is a proposal for logging corresponding request IDs together, so users
can easily lookup the request IDs of services other than the one the user
called directly.

blueprint log-request-id-mappings

Change-Id: Ib9b820a0feeb0c0e828ed3e4fab8261f8761ba9a

subject: Haproxy should listen only on vip
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-04-22 12:48:44.000000000', 'files': ['elements/haproxy/os-config-applier/etc/haproxy/haproxy.cfg', 'elements/haproxy/README.md'], 'message': 'Haproxy should listen only on vip

Adding ability for haproxy to listen only on specifically configured
vip interface

It will enable setups where using different ports for balancer service
is not convenient, e.g:

listen horizon
  bind 192.168.0.2:80
  balance  source
  mode  http
  server node-1 192.168.0.3:80 cookie node-1  check inter 2000 fall 3
  server node-2 192.168.0.4:80 cookie node-2  check inter 2000 fall 3
  server node-3 192.168.0.5:80 cookie node-3  check inter 2000 fall 3

Related to blueprint tripleo-icehouse-ha-production-configuration

Change-Id: Ifd441a1d5fb50d0cfb16dc4197caf2c1912cf1ab
'}]
commit_message:
Haproxy should listen only on vip

Adding ability for haproxy to listen only on specifically configured
vip interface

It will enable setups where using different ports for balancer service
is not convenient, e.g:

listen horizon
  bind 192.168.0.2:80
  balance  source
  mode  http
  server node-1 192.168.0.3:80 cookie node-1  check inter 2000 fall 3
  server node-2 192.168.0.4:80 cookie node-2  check inter 2000 fall 3
  server node-3 192.168.0.5:80 cookie node-3  check inter 2000 fall 3

Related to blueprint tripleo-icehouse-ha-production-configuration

commit_message:
XenAPI: Use local rsync rather than remote if possible

Using ssh depends on the host being set up to be able to SSH into
itself which is not a common scenario.  While this is unavoidable for
the current implementation of resize across multiple hosts, if there
is a single host (i.e. a test scenario) or the resize is restricted
to the same host then we can succeed without SSH access

Dependency on Ia310e31d31aaf5c979e41c64af8223202a18e03a is because the
tests will always fail without Ia310 therefore this fix cannot be tested
without taking Ia310 as well.

Closes-bug: 1308064

Change-Id: I15802a1d97d380b1c5b74fc9f92ece2494fe789a

commit_message:
RabbitMQ - Consistent PID file location

Ubuntu and RabbitMQ's rabbitmq-server packages use different
default PID file locations. We should explicitly choose a single
location to use.

Change-Id: Ia9d1fb55bbca02609396e8f1e163abef61398d54

commit_message:
Fix the parameter order of assertEqual in glanceclient v2 test

On assertEqual, the order of parameters should be (expected, observed).
But, some part of glanceclient v2 test were written with invalid order.
This patch fixes this problem.

Partially Close-bug: #1277104

Change-Id: Iae3fb9dda28b67a07f527b15ca83d9cca3e867d4

Add a _disk_size_from_instance method which by using the disk name
determine the size of the disk refered in the instance properties.
Update the method finish_migration to use this new helper.

commit_message:
Verify delete interface response of V2/V3 APIs

This patch adds the JSON schema for response status of Nova interface delete
APIs to block the backward incompatibility change in the future.

delete interface does not return the response body.
Response status of above APIs is 202 in v2/v3.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I8ff4f3e2b8912d29918965b4aa86cf807a9a23ca

commit_message:
Xen: Retry plugin call after connection reset

When using the call_plugin_serialized_with_retry session method it will
retry if the plugin raises a RetryableError, but not if it loses the
connection to xenapi.  This adds a retry for the 'Connection reset by
peer' error that is occasionally seen.

Change-Id: Ibb36a0170e0e807ad7a4198df7b6e574c4279bed
Closes-Bug: #1200591

subject: Disable reverse dns lookup
revisions:
[{'number': 9, 'created': '2014-04-23 02:18:45.000000000', 'files': ['ceilometer/api/app.py', 'ceilometer/api/__init__.py'], 'message': 'Disable reverse dns lookup

The BaseHTTPServer will do a reverse dns lookup when log message, which
will cause 10 seconds latency in some network environment. This will
significantly slow down the api request when wsgiref.simple_server is
used.

This patch creates a class, which inherits from
simple_server.WSGIRequestHandler but overrides address_string method,
and passes it to handler_class param of simple_server.make_server.

Change-Id: Ia38c7719ed700ab5867dcc4bcf3700bff282a907
Closes-Bug: #1291229
'}]
commit_message:
Disable reverse dns lookup

The BaseHTTPServer will do a reverse dns lookup when log message, which
will cause 10 seconds latency in some network environment. This will
significantly slow down the api request when wsgiref.simple_server is
used.

This patch creates a class, which inherits from
simple_server.WSGIRequestHandler but overrides address_string method,
and passes it to handler_class param of simple_server.make_server.

Change-Id: Ia38c7719ed700ab5867dcc4bcf3700bff282a907
Closes-Bug: #1291229

commit_message:
Fallback to None on missing Glance image attrs

It's possible for glance images to be missing attributes like name and
checksum. We'll just set those to None by default to avoid missing key
exceptions being raised.

When the keystone tokens backend is SQL, the tokens table grows

commit_message:
Add crontab to flush tokens via keystone-manage

When the keystone tokens backend is SQL, the tokens table grows
unboundedly as new tokens are issued and not disposed of after
expiration.

Keystone provides a tool to delete the tokens, and this patch puts it in
a cronjob in order to avoid growing the tokens database forever.

Change-Id: I3e4831619efec273ac5aa378fff4b14ad877f326
Implements: blueprint token-flush

commit_message:
Allow trollius 0.2

As the author of Trollius, I'm asking to allow the new release because I want
to use it in pending patches.

Trollius 0.2 is compatible with 0.1.6. Trollius 0.2 has the (almost the) same
API than asyncio in Python 3.4 (will should be released next week end) and
Tulip 0.4.1. After the final release of Python 3.4, backward incompatible
changes are no more allowed, so there is no need to restrict Trollius version
to < 0.2.

Trollius 0.2 uses the syntax "yield From(...)" instead of "yield ...", but the
old syntax is still allowed.

Anyway, right now, no OpenStack component use Trollius. Pending patches:

* https://review.openstack.org/#/c/70948/ : patch written for Trollus 0.1, but
  it works on Trollius 0.2 too. I will update the patch to require Trollius 0.2
  and use "yield From(...)"
* https://review.openstack.org/#/c/77925/ : tests are failing because this
  patch requires Trollius 0.2, that's why I would like to upgrade Trollius

I also moved trollius to the right section of dependencies. Sorry, I didn't
noticed first that dependencies were grouped.

Trollius has now a much better documentation:
http://trollius.readthedocs.org/

Change-Id: I7b23262a728119350133becef18058242553a03c

commit_message:
Implement testing of migrations

Dependences: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/42307/ (should be reviewed).

This patch adds opportunity of migrations testing.
By this test each migration checks on mysql/postgres dialects in
upgrade > downgrade> upgrade mode.
Also models are tested to equality with actual database state.
In this patch an opportunity of testing migrations adds.
We just need to add _pre_upgrade_NUM, _check_NUM, _post_downgrade_NUM
methods with number of migration (NUM).
It works for both of repos (migrate and alembic).

Models will be tested on different things:
- columns (type, length, nullable),
- constraints (indexes, unique keys, foreign keys),
- list of tables.

This patch contains a check methods for 15 migration as a sample.

bp: ceilometer-db-sync-models-with-migrations

Change-Id: I3b0651d1b29f0a85f7872f0982b7240989abbef3

commit_message:
Add testing of migrations from oslo

There is a testing of migrations in oslo.
We can check equality of models with migrations in different
backends. Also we can check an each migration in full mode
(upgrade > downgrade > upgrade).
Migrate and alembic repos can be tested together.
We have only sqlite testing of migrations in upgrade mode now.
But there are a lot of bugs that can be visible in other
dialects. Also a lot of migrations that can have mistakes in downgrade.
So we should have both of these tests in ceilometer for successfull
checking of migrations.

Dependences: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/42307/
             https://review.openstack.org/#/c/53612/

bp: db-common-migration-and-utils

Change-Id: I477e3593aef4119cb04f95d0dcbaef21f90e3083

commit_message:
Detect selinux passwd setting bug

If on a Fedora, CentOS or RHEL system w/ SELinux enabled (even
permissive), bug 1292614 will be hit. This change stops the user
up front instead of deep into the image creation.

commit_message:
Logical error in blockless fanout of zmq

The blockless fanout doesn't take effect and it only processes
the FIRST one by returning after the first loop.

Change-Id: I8ddb80011be1965f3576331b6fd9e17f783d268f
Closes-Bug: #1293092

commit_message:
Added function to deal with deadlock in tests

Added new method used in fake threads during test. Method catch deadlock
and retry operation in FakeDeletionThread. Removed skipping of
problematic test.

Closes-Bug: #1308115

commit_message:
Break Identity API into v2 and v3 pages

Add authenticate call to first page of api ref
Fix titles to match correct API versions
Added forward slash to beginning of all API calls
Added neutron to occurrences of OpenStack Networking
Other clean up

Change-Id: Ifcb51efa5996d083d9e6099c9b72b8faf39707b2
author: diane fleming

commit_message:
Make Search query ignore current category

Search should be run against all possible categories, otherwise it is
much less useful. So, after user submits Search request,
current_category will be set to 'All'. Also page navigation for
multi-paged search results is fixed (it didn't work earlier).

Change-Id: I556fa7cc23f4c004047c36d8aa11097a21a2d477
Closes-Bug: #1307931

commit_message:
Allow settings for Nova Scheduler

This change is to allow settings for nova scheduler:

scheduler_available_filters
  Filter classes available to the scheduler which may be specified more
  than once.

scheduler_default_filters
  Which filter class names to use for filtering hosts when not specified
  in the request.

scheduler_weight_classes
  Which weight class names to use for weighing hosts.

scheduler_driver
  Default driver to use for the scheduler.

scheduler_host_subset_size
  New instances will be scheduled on a host chosen randomly from a subset of
  the N best hosts. This property defines the  subset size that a host is
  chosen from.

Change-Id: Ia622ad4d64b298f0a8dc3cb0b9ba1561862b7f23

commit_message:
Allow settings for Nova API

Allow settings for:

osapi_compute_workers
  - Number of workers for OpenStack API service. The default will be the
    number of CPUs available. (integer value)

osapi_compute_extension
  - osapi compute extension to load.

osapi_compute_ext_list
  - Specify list of extensions to load when using
    osapi_compute_extension option with
    nova.api.openstack.compute.contrib.select_extensions.

multi_instance_display_name_template
  - Template used to build the display name for instances created using a
    single request via os-multiple-create API extension.

Change-Id: I47460fa7fbbf40aa72c7ebafd9e5c00ebf0c6b7b

commit_message:
Adding libvirt options for injection and rescue

This change is adding some specific options to configure the file injection and
the rescue image ids to be used for rescuing an instance:
inject_partition
  - The partition to inject to: -2 => disable, -1 => inspect
    (libguestfs only), 0 => not partitioned, >0 => partition
rescue_image_id
  - Rescue ami image
rescue_kernel_id
  - Rescue aki image
rescue_ramdisk_id
  - Rescue ari image

Change-Id: I338a67b695bb4cf160ef5e2f326e60fa900a4fd3

commit_message:
Make time out 60 mins like the Heat default.

Make the undercloud create timeout match that of the Heat default
(60 mins for the Heat stack-create), as on slow networks with real
hardware the set-up time can be slow. Also if the stack-create
fails the loop will exit so this change should be harmless.

Change-Id: Iec8aafb73f0b9da72ae9a94d9a4e7c91bd29e496

commit_message:
run_tests.sh improvements

1. Run shotgun's tests

2. Write XUnit data to separate files

   Since now, the `run_tests.sh` writes XUnit XMLs as separate files.
   Both filenames and paths could be overridden by setuping next env variables:

   * NAILGUN_XUNIT                  (default: nailgun.xml)
   * FUELCLIENT_XUNIT               (default: fuelclient.xml)
   * FUELUPGRADE_XUNIT              (default: fuelupgrade.xml)
   * FUELUPGRADEDOWNLOADER_XUNIT    (default: fuelupgradedownloader.xml)
   * SHOTGUN_XUNIT                  (default: shotgun.xml)

   Example:

       NAILGUN_XUNIT="~/reports/nailgun.xml" ./run_tests.sh --with-xunit

Closes-Bug: #1304361
Closes-Bug: #1311073

Change-Id: I60e7733ed4c85e6decb29635d55e3ec8befa8ee1

commit_message:
begin conversion to rst

This converts 2 of the reference documents to rst, and fixes the
tox.ini so that tox -e docs creates a pretty html version of these
documents. While the publish target location has still not been
sorted this moves the ball forward in generating nicer output
for the documents.

The incubation-integration-requirements document was intentionally
left out, because it's much more active, and we should decide this
is the right approach before we impose the merge conflicts on
everyone in flight.

Change-Id: I2fefdb5efe196cdbda4555141b09e7e771e20bdd

commit_message:
Use "https" instead of "git" for cloning code

If you're in a private network, you need to setup a proxy
to access the public network. It would be a difficult thing
to set-up proxy for git:// protocol, while much more easy to
use https:// protocol instead.

Change-Id: Iec8447cc28760a98e1641162c50c152c89100775

subject: Fix tempest_*_id_setter to query the RAL and cache
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 3153, 'name': 'Emilien Macchi', 'email': 'emilien@redhat.com', 'username': 'emilienm'}, {'_account_id': 7822, 'name': 'Chris Hoge (not involved in upstream development)', 'email': 'chris@hogepodge.com', 'username': 'hogepodge'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-04-11 00:43:24.000000000', 'files': ['lib/puppet/provider/tempest_neutron_net_id_setter/ruby.rb', 'lib/puppet/provider/tempest_glance_id_setter/ruby.rb'], 'message': "Fix tempest_*_id_setter to query the RAL and cache

The tempest_glance_id_setter previously would query the catalog for the
id of a glance_image resource with a given name. This doesn't work on a
split-node openstack where tempest is not on the glance host. It would
also fail horribly if glance-api.conf didn't exist.

The tempest_neutron_id_setter previously would query the instances of
neutron network IDs from the RAL once for every line in the tempest.conf
file if the network did not exist (because the cache would be nil).

Now they both query the RAL directly from the system, similar to how
tempest_neutron_id_setter did it but using Puppet::Resource.indirection,
but don't continue requerying for every line in the tempest.conf when
the given resource title doesn't yet exist, and tempest_glance_id_setter
raises a helpful error if the glance-api.conf file does not exist.

Change-Id: Icdca2c1a5f449b3fcda68d43a34452cd119303cb
"}]
commit_message:
Fix tempest_*_id_setter to query the RAL and cache

The tempest_glance_id_setter previously would query the catalog for the
id of a glance_image resource with a given name. This doesn't work on a
split-node openstack where tempest is not on the glance host. It would
also fail horribly if glance-api.conf didn't exist.

The tempest_neutron_id_setter previously would query the instances of
neutron network IDs from the RAL once for every line in the tempest.conf
file if the network did not exist (because the cache would be nil).

Now they both query the RAL directly from the system, similar to how
tempest_neutron_id_setter did it but using Puppet::Resource.indirection,
but don't continue requerying for every line in the tempest.conf when
the given resource title doesn't yet exist, and tempest_glance_id_setter
raises a helpful error if the glance-api.conf file does not exist.

Change-Id: Icdca2c1a5f449b3fcda68d43a34452cd119303cb

commit_message:
Update quota when instance stuck to DELETING

The only place we ever update quotas as part of delete should
be when the instance DB record is removed. If something is
stuck in DELETING, it means that the quota was not updated.
We should make sure we're always updating the quota when
the instance DB record is removed.

Change-Id: I7debe92fb815393830cf59dc309c6a0af9d0152e
Partial-Bug: #1296414

commit_message:
dry_run can be optional

node_remove.rb is not sending this parameter, so if it is not optional,
there would be error like:

MC agent 'erase_node', method 'erase_node', results:
{
    :sender=>"2", :statuscode=>4,
    :statusmsg=>"Action 'erase_node' needs a 'dry_run' argument",
    :data=>
    {
        :status=>nil, :erased=>nil, :error_msg=>nil, :debug_msg=>nil,
        :rebooted=>nil
    }
}

Change-Id: I2d6115c2a7c1ed765e34b03bc1907c2fd5204002

commit_message:
Make heat default infrastructure engine

We're running heat-based savanna-ci jobs for a while and heat
integration seems mostly completed. So, let's enable it by default and
then direct (savanna) infrastructure engine will be ready for removal in
Juno release cycle.

commit_message:
Allow setting the location of VM swapfile for libvirtDriver

Add support to set the location of virtual machine swap files separately
for libvirtDriver. With such a feature enabled, swapfiles can be placed onto
a specified storage, e.g. a SSD, separately, that improve the performance
of guest VM.

Related to blueprint set-vm-swapfile-location.

Change-Id: Icc917a26a0ac797d8496ead320144bb8078462fb

commit_message:
Don't slugify() None names

If image has no name, human_id can't be built.
Also slugify raises ValueError if None argument passed.
It affects Docker images.

This is a copy of Change Ib975775b here:

https://review.openstack.org/65665

The original change was made against python-novaclient and then
subsequently overwritten when resynced with oslo-incubator.  This
reapplies the change, except within oslo-incubator this time.

Change-Id: If9f1b42bc028b314ff030ef063bffee656507625

commit_message:
Compatibility with Pep8 1.5.4+

Pep8 1.5.4+ fixes various bugs in space/indentation detection,
so accommodate for those:

  E128 continuation line under-indented for visual indent
  E123 closing bracket does not match indentation of opening bracket's
  line
  E251 unexpected spaces around keyword / parameter equals
  E714 test for object identity should be 'is not'
  E713 test for membership should be 'not in'
  E265 block comment should start with '# '

Change-Id: I5b1daac701dd53a0f639583a61404429dd2161fe

subject: escape and encode HTTP headers
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-03-25 17:29:38.000000000', 'files': ['glanceclient/v1/images.py'], 'message': 'escape and encode HTTP headers

The v1 glanceclient takes various user input for image metadata and
encodes it as HTTP headers.  Some level of armoring against
malice/incompetence should be done here.  e.g., the
"x-image-meta-property-description" header is a free-form text
field, and can have newlines, but passing in newlines breaks
everything, and leaves the API prone to injection attacks.

Change-Id: I3f0fbda47f5392b00d152d58ef1d94ce034eadf5
Partial-Bug: 1297414
'}]
commit_message:
escape and encode HTTP headers

The v1 glanceclient takes various user input for image metadata and
encodes it as HTTP headers.  Some level of armoring against
malice/incompetence should be done here.  e.g., the
"x-image-meta-property-description" header is a free-form text
field, and can have newlines, but passing in newlines breaks
everything, and leaves the API prone to injection attacks.

Change-Id: I3f0fbda47f5392b00d152d58ef1d94ce034eadf5
Partial-Bug: 1297414

commit_message:
Change volume retype behavior when driver raise exception

When modifying volume type, if driver returns False stand for
the driver not support it, then the operation will fall back
to generic mechanism.

But if driver raises exception, should report error and set
volume status as "error".

Change-Id: Icc9421a331b094049242c4115d9f08b318a6f99c
Closes-Bug: #1305550

commit_message:
Check attributes of attach/detach volume Nova APIs

This patch adds the JSON schema for attach and detach volume Nova
V2 & V3 APIs and validate the response of Nova attach and detach Volume
APIs with added JSON schema to block the backward incompatibility
change in the future.

Response body of V2 attach volume-

{
    "volumeAttachment": {
        "id": "a26887c6-c47b-4654-abb5-dfadf7d3f803",
        "device": "/dev/vdd",
        "volumeId": "a26887c6-c47b-4654-abb5-dfadf7d3f803",
        "serverId": "0c92f3f6-c253-4c9b-bd43-e880a8d2eb0a"
    }
}

Response body of V2 detach Volume-
Empty response body
Status code -202

Response body of V3 attach & detach volume-
Empty response body
Status code -202

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I8139bfba3e303c2aba1e78519e3470e86929d268

commit_message:
Configurable token hash algorithm

Tokens were always hashed with MD5. This change allows tokens to
be hashed with SHA256 (or any other algorithm supported by the
keystoneclient token hash function). This is for security
hardening.

There's a new configuration option 'hash_algorithm' in the [token]
section. This is the algorithm to use for hashing PKI tokens, so is
used

a) when storing the token in the db
b) as the hash in the revocation list

hash_algorithm defaults to 'md5' for backwards compatibility.

SecurityImpact
DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1174499

Change-Id: Iafe3c975d59818c8f362647f7ea5149a03deee47

commit_message:
Wire in _EXTRA_INSTALL_OPTS...

Updates the various environment.d elements so that we can control
with a high level of granularity whether we enable
--system-site-packages in our virtualenvs. At a high level
OPENSTACK_EXTRA_INSTALL_OPTS can be set to -s to allow
os-svc-install to enable --system-site-packages globally.
The per element environment variables if set will override this
setting.

A step towards supporting both isolated and global venvs
for OpenStack elements installed from git source.

Change-Id: Ic3dc42717a90f02a58af345c5564336b64f930e4

I've seen several folks recently have problems with their Swift
clusters because they had different hash prefixes on different
nodes. Let's help them out by having recon check that.

Note that MD5-equality is stronger than what we need (which is
ConfigParser-equality for a particular set of keys), but this way we

commit_message:
Check swift.conf MD5 with recon

I've seen several folks recently have problems with their Swift
clusters because they had different hash prefixes on different
nodes. Let's help them out by having recon check that.

Note that MD5-equality is stronger than what we need (which is
ConfigParser-equality for a particular set of keys), but this way we
don't expose the secret hash prefix and suffix across the internal
network, just the MD5 checksum of the file containing them.

Change-Id: I3af984ee45947345891b3c596a88e3464f178cc7

commit_message:
Verify the response attributes of 'update-aggregate' API

This patch verifies the response attributes of 'update-aggregate'.
The response body of v2 and v3 API has the same format:
{
    "aggregate": {
        "availability_zone": "nova2",
        "created_at": "2013-08-18T12:17:56.259751",
        "deleted": false,
        "deleted_at": null,
        "hosts": [],
        "id": 1,
        "metadata": {
            "availability_zone": "nova2"
        },
        "name": "newname",
        "updated_at": "2013-08-18T12:17:56.286720"
    }
}
This patch also fixes a typo bug of the schema.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I89547d8069aae9d2ad0b4cd081843865f42bc4e7

commit_message:
Skip more pause tests if pause is not available

There are several compute API tests that attempt to pause a server but
should be skipped if the pause feature is not enabled.

Note that there are some negative tests which call the pause API but on
invalid server states, i.e. non-existent server, unpausing a server
that's not paused, etc, but those shouldn't get down to the virt driver
so we don't need to skip them since they should fail in the Nova API
service, not in the compute service.

Related-Bug: #1296858

Change-Id: I6f74c17af2c7540f913b71350770be7f004769a9

commit_message:
Optional data for resource_data_get_all

resource_data_get_all queries the database for the data, and
transforms the results to a decrypted dict.

If the data is already loaded then it is unnecessary to do the
database query again.

This change allows data to be passed in as an optional argument.
If the passed data is not None then no database call will be made
and the dict transformation will occur on passed data.

Change-Id: I579225d9a3f3b038e0ca41a5900c58413d6e25ac
Related-Bug: #1306743

commit_message:
Enable flake8 E711 and E712 checking

E711 comparison to False should be 'if cond is False:' or 'if not cond:'
     comparison to None should be 'if cond is None:' or 'if not cond:'
E712 comparison to True should be 'if cond is True:' or 'if cond:'

Most violations were in DB queries. Replace as follows:
  False -> sqlalchemy.sql.false()
  None  -> sqlalchemy.sql.null()
  True  -> sqlalchemy.sql.true()

Change-Id: Iff54747b70f504d5466cfdc6e2ec4d7a0f9ddb7c
Closes-bug: #1305377

commit_message:
Don't translate debug level scheduler logs

Our translation policy
(https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LoggingStandards#Log_Translation) calls
for not translating debug level logs. This is to help prioritize log
translation. Furthermore translation has a performance overhead, even if
the log isn't used (since nova doesn't support lazy translation yet).

Remove unnecessary debug level log translation in the scheduler to
comply with our translation policy. This has the added benefit of making
the scheduler slightly faster too.

Add a local hacking rule to enforce this.

Change-Id: Ie1068d2d2c7c37f27c62d0e4e5a64a1a504af9f5

commit_message:
Correct hard-coded IP ranges

If a baremetal-network is provided in the environment settings
passed to devtest, not all IP ranges are set correctly as some are
hard-coded. This patch makes it so that the environment settings
are used if available.

Relates to: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/85446/

Change-Id: I11ed72a1427f110568f47590a29446d5945b8cbd
Co-Author: matthew.gilliard@hp.com

[{'number': 11, 'created': '2014-04-22 12:10:19.000000000', 'files': ['nailgun/nailgun/objects/node.py', 'nailgun/nailgun/network/manager.py', 'nailgun/nailgun/test/unit/test_node_nic_handler.py', 'nailgun/nailgun/api/handlers/node.py'], 'message': "Don't update NIC info, if metadata is incorrect

Sometimes our discovery agent tries to post a new metadata with missed NICs.
In that case, nailgun used to remove NICs from the database, even those with

in serialization phase and so on.

commit_message:
Don't update NIC info, if metadata is incorrect

Sometimes our discovery agent tries to post a new metadata with missed NICs.
In that case, nailgun used to remove NICs from the database, even those with
assigned network roles. This leads to bad consequences, such as an exceptions
in serialization phase and so on.

Since now, if a NIC has assigned network roles, it won't be removed from
the database, even if a new metadata has been received without that NIC.
So we just log a warning message and print a traceback to logs.

Closes-Bug: #1282568
Change-Id: I5658379587d2adec4b5baa0419aca4659bdb7883

migrate_instance_finish() methods that are still hitting the database

commit_message:
Add worker threads limit to _check_deploy_timeouts task

New nodes filter parameters added to db.sqlalchemy.api. This
parameters used in _check_deploy_timeouts periodic task for
limit of worker threads which can be started simultaneously.
New config option 'periodic_max_workers' added to conductor
group.

Closes-Bug: #1285793
Change-Id: I646540e334dec05682640c05cedb315e0ee355bc

commit_message:
Fix RGW endpoint port

Change RGW endpoint port registered in keystone
to 8080 as this is the real port on which
haproxy is listening.

Previously, until https://review.openstack.org/#/c/85195/
was merged, RGW was working because virtual IP was located
on one of the controllers and apache proxying RGW fastcgi
application was answering on 6780 port. Currently, VIP moved
into namespace and 6780 is no longer available.

Change-Id: Ib5c20760af7c20a5b2b45fcc899cdc113845ea3f
Closes-Bug: #1307508

commit_message:
Describe addresses in ec2 api broken with neutron

It attempts to retrieve the fixed ip directly,
but it's not supported by neutron.

After the modification,
the instance uuid will be pulled without using get_fixed_ip().

Change-Id: Ia1b95d4c18aeb5012919af89148947694d80e2e7
Closes-Bug: #1273837

commit_message:
Discourage use of pki_setup

After a mailing list discussion it is clear that users need more
information to make a decision on how to setup their PKI tokens.

This recommends an external CA over using keystone pki_setup as it does
offer a bit more protection against an intruder being able to setup a
rogue token generator.

Change-Id: I798a562dd8c222e04660482b434ed3bbe6b63d62

commit_message:
Rename ironic option drivers_whitelist -> enabled_drivers

commit_message:
Use eventlet.tpool.Proxy for DB API calls

There is no eventlet in common db code anymore, so, if we want to use
thread pooling for DB API calls, we should use eventlet.tpool.Proxy()
instead of tpool_wrapper() from openstack.common.db.api.

Config option CONF.database.use_tpool was moved from module
nova.openstack.common.db.api to nova.db.api.
Config file `nova.conf.sample` was updated as well.

See also patch to Oslo - I6fa140f2b1f03c43ae7cab98ac8a12d71188af76

Co-Authored-By: Chris Behrens <cbehrens@codestud.com>
Change-Id: Id7de85dce11f5ea61dfccddf80de7800a2bc4e37

commit_message:
Idiomatic -d (debug) flag

It's common for a flag's presence to signal a feature is enable and
it's absence to signal disabled. This patch switches '-d true/false'
to simply '-d' or no '-d'.

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-04-14 17:59:19.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/api/openstack/compute/test_servers.py', 'nova/tests/api/openstack/compute/plugins/v3/test_servers.py', 'nova/api/openstack/compute/views/servers.py'], 'message': 'GET details REST API next link missing 'details'

When executing a pagination query a "next" link is included in the
API reply when there are more items then the specified limit.

See pagination documentation for more information:
http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2/content/
Paginated_Collections-d1e664.html

The caller should be able to invoke the "next" link (without
having to re-format it) in order to get the next page of data.
The documentation states "Subsequent links will honor the
initial page size. Thus, a client may follow links to traverse
a paginated collection without having to input the marker parameter."

The problem is that the "next" link is always scoped to the
non-detailed query.

For example, if you execute "/v2/<tenant>/servers/detail?limit=1",
the "next" link does not have the URL for a detailed query and is
formatted as "/v2/<tenant>/servers?limit=1&marker=<marker>". In this
case the "next" link needs to be scoped to "/v2/<tenant>/servers/detail".
Common code is used for both the v2 and v3 APIs.

Existing test cases will be updated to verify that the next link is
correctly scoped for both the v2 and v3 APIs.

The user could work around this issue my manually inserting '/details'
into the "next" link URL.

Change-Id: Ib06a6cc6e2dd5e2c8c16986ee256a58752626eb9
Closes-bug: 1299247
'}]
commit_message:
GET details REST API next link missing 'details'

When executing a pagination query a "next" link is included in the
API reply when there are more items then the specified limit.

See pagination documentation for more information:
http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2/content/
Paginated_Collections-d1e664.html

The caller should be able to invoke the "next" link (without
having to re-format it) in order to get the next page of data.
The documentation states "Subsequent links will honor the
initial page size. Thus, a client may follow links to traverse
a paginated collection without having to input the marker parameter."

The problem is that the "next" link is always scoped to the
non-detailed query.

For example, if you execute "/v2/<tenant>/servers/detail?limit=1",
the "next" link does not have the URL for a detailed query and is
formatted as "/v2/<tenant>/servers?limit=1&marker=<marker>". In this
case the "next" link needs to be scoped to "/v2/<tenant>/servers/detail".
Common code is used for both the v2 and v3 APIs.

Existing test cases will be updated to verify that the next link is
correctly scoped for both the v2 and v3 APIs.

The user could work around this issue my manually inserting '/details'
into the "next" link URL.

Change-Id: Ib06a6cc6e2dd5e2c8c16986ee256a58752626eb9
Closes-bug: 1299247

commit_message:
ec2: use SecurityGroup object

Convert one place in the ec2 API code that was using the db API
directly to get a security group.  Use the SecurityGroup object for
this instead.

Some test fixes were needed to account for fields that the
SecurityGroup object does not have set as nullable.

Change-Id: I4b15b6bcb35f95955911a48faa8d74f6167593a0

commit_message:
Validate IPv6 modes in API when IP version is 4

Add a validation to ipv6_ra_mode and ipv6_address_mode with ip
version. An InvalidInput error is prompted when ipv6_ra_mode
or ipv6_address_mode is specified in subnet create and update
API and ip version is 4.

Change-Id: I9a0356f23e6b162c31f2d289a34f4bd261cee91e
Closes-Bug: 1307788

commit_message:
Add unit tests for all generators

generate_json.py does not exist any longer. Using the checks there
and move them into test_negative_generators.py. From now on the checks
are usable for all generators (also valid_generator) using a base class.

In order to check for unknown types it was mandatory to change an
existing exception to a more detailed exception (TypeError).

Partially implements bp unit-tests

Change-Id: I6b5b66f8ae113c1aca471d8338334cd47ff45723

commit_message:
Neutron Nova Interactions Support

Recent versions of Neutron are able to provide active notifications to
Nova about changes to port status and data.  This change adds the
neutron::server::notifications class to allow Puppet to configure this
feature when setting up a Neutron server.

neutron.conf requires a tenant UUID for communicating with Nova.  This
changes adds adds a custom type and provider to translate an admin
tenant name to the required UUID.

Co-Authored-By: emilienm <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>
Change-Id: I57af7cb47a12adabed9b1ee65e1c352b3e5fc2de
Closes-bug: 1306694

commit_message:
Send gratuitous arp on ns_ipaddr2 start

Send gratuitous arps on the host node
after ip address is started using
ns_IPaddr2 resource agent
Script sends 5 gratuitous/unsolicited ARP
packets every 200 milliseconds from the
NIC of corresponding interface with
source IP set to the corresponding IP

Change-Id: I1a1b8079e93c5d4cd2ab9b6b17f7686160950734
Closes-bug: #1310676

commit_message:
Support for v2 agent payloads

The agent is now sending more data, which changed the schema. This
supports the new interfaces layout. Support for the rest of the
payload (CPU/Mem/etc) will come in a separate patch, along with
refactoring v0-v2.

Change-Id: I5da8310257fb720fa9fc67fb030fe0c57718a8f1

This allows the nova driver to ask nova to create a configdrive for an
instance, compress it, base64 encoding it, and store it in the Ironic DB. Then the
agent will be able to download and decode the configdrive, then write it
to the disk. Configdrive allows Nova to set the root password, static
networking on an instance, and inject files.

commit_message:
Add configdrive generation to Nova driver

This allows the nova driver to ask nova to create a configdrive for an
instance, compress it, base64 encoding it, and store it in the Ironic DB. Then the
agent will be able to download and decode the configdrive, then write it
to the disk. Configdrive allows Nova to set the root password, static
networking on an instance, and inject files.

Change-Id: I64f6ae7ff9403d99a9ff5d035a37d0ec5a3f74cf

commit_message:
Correct default usage filtering on overview page

On the overview page, the usage data showed by default was not filtered by
the dates shown on the date selectors. This can lead the user to wrong
conclusions about resource usage.

This patch corrects the default filtering dates to match the dates showed
by default on overview (first day in the month to current date).

Change-Id: I37a240d784ca0826821c125f06922d2c1d1e8659
Closes-Bug: #1294668

commit_message:
Consume notif. from multiple message bus

This patch allow to consume notification from multiple
message bus servers at the same times with configuration like:

 [DEFAULT]
 transport_url = rabbit://rabbit-ceilo:5772/

 [notification]
 messaging_urls = rabbit://rabbit-nova1:5772,rabbit-nova2:5772/
 messaging_urls = rabbit://rabbit-cinder:5772/
 messaging_urls = rabbit://rabbit-neutron:5772/

Implements blueprint multiple-rabbitmq

Co-Authored-By: Ala Rezmerita <ala.rezmerita@cloudwatt.com>

Change-Id: If3bf6f080ce15f2403c3516b433953b0bdf6ea40

commit_message:
Fix mongo db nodes collection

We should not put a comma at the end of mongo db nodes list.
Because current mongo implementation supports max 3 mongo nodes,
fix the cases for # of mongo nodes < 3.

Closes-bug: #1311088

Change-Id: I5276aa71b3a637cb485983ec13ebcd83f8add5fc
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

subject: Make pull-tools ignore errors if USE_CACHE is set.
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-04-22 01:55:58.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/pull-tools'], 'message': "Make pull-tools ignore errors if USE_CACHE is set.

If I'm trying to work offline and I've set USE_CACHE, it seems odd that
pull-tools will abort a run because it can't talk to the git server.

This change makse it simply continue if a git pull fails. This is
potentially too broad (eg, it would ignore errors caused by the local
repo being corrupt, or a ff-only merge not being possible.
)

Change-Id: I9d6329567bdf7f0725624fca3b58cd9487e3d7c3
"}]
commit_message:
Make pull-tools ignore errors if USE_CACHE is set.

If I'm trying to work offline and I've set USE_CACHE, it seems odd that
pull-tools will abort a run because it can't talk to the git server.

This change makse it simply continue if a git pull fails. This is
potentially too broad (eg, it would ignore errors caused by the local
repo being corrupt, or a ff-only merge not being possible.
)

Change-Id: I9d6329567bdf7f0725624fca3b58cd9487e3d7c3

Downgrade the log from error to debug and after all, user can

commit_message:
Downgrade the log level when automatic confirm_resize fails

When CONF.resize_confirm_window is not 0, the unconfirmed migration
will be confirmed automatically after CONF.resize_confirm_window
seconds; it might fail due to reason such as instance is locked etc,
so failed to automatically confirm resize is not unexpected.
Downgrade the log from error to debug and after all, user can
either confirm it later or next automatically confirm might success.
Also modify the format of log as well.

Change-Id: I525c803d5e149c49606bcd460e2abb4c9300454a

commit_message:
Wait 10 sec for receiving sended packets

There is some randomness in results of network verification
in slow networks environment

As fix we need to wait some time between sending and polling listeners
for received packets, it wont be an issue because verification now very fast

commit_message:
Raise error on nova-api if missing subnets/fixed_ips on networks/port

Previously, if one would launch an instance on a network that did not contain
any subnets or on a port that did not have a fixedip the instance would fail
to boot resulting in a SecurityGroupCannotBeApplied  on the nova-compute node.
This patch adds checks to validate networks so it fails on nova-api and
the user will be able to see why from the response.

Note: a patch to fix the neutron port-security-enabled extension will
follow which allows one to boot instances on networks without subnets
and ports without fixedips.

Change-Id: I104d5234b34726e5f5819fc2a81eef55e3c70f42
Closes-bug: 1252410

commit_message:
Bring agent deploy driver up to date with virt

This uses the `image_source` and `configdrive` fields added here:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/86192/

It also looks up image info from glance based on the image ID.
The boot device is properly set and the node is rebooted.

Also removes duplicate test that was broken by this change.

Change-Id: I2a4079d04bd6896b1b1a6bebec719925f145c7cc

commit_message:
Sends notifications at lease events

Climate now uses oslo.notify to send notifications when
CRUD lease operations are executed and when relevant lease
events happen (start_lease, before_end_lease, end_lease).
This implementation also adds one new event type called
before_end_lease to be sent when a lease is close to be ended.
Moreover, a new oslo.notify wrapper class was also added.

Change-Id: I861540e5ec5d1309ded2de56b2135bae5b59dad9
Implements: blueprint notifications

commit_message:
Fixed diagnostic snapshot generation for master node

* shlex in python 2.6 was broken and doesn't
  work correct with unicode, we have to
  encode it to ascii explicitly
* fixed strings formating, use format
  method
* fixed tests, use assertEqual instead of
  buildin assert method

Closes-bug: #1310927
Change-Id: I4a0746791d4317571d882416cfe75e8a41edf08a

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-04-17 18:26:03.000000000', 'files': ['hacking/core.py', 'requirements.txt', 'HACKING.rst'], 'message': "Move hacking to pep8 1.5.6

pep8 1.5.x drastically changed the way comments and docstrings are
handled. Previously docstrings and comments weren't tokenized so we had
to do some extra work to parse them ourselves, but now that they are
tokenized the appropriate hacking rules to use the new
tokenized text.

Also update all doctests and HACKING.rst to add space after '#' in
'# TODO'.

Note: the hacking code changes won't work with pep8 1.4.6, so the code
and dependency are both changed at the same time.

Change-Id: Ib35d493309fe7e87112a94c74beb70054ca0655c
"}]
commit_message:
Move hacking to pep8 1.5.6

pep8 1.5.x drastically changed the way comments and docstrings are
handled. Previously docstrings and comments weren't tokenized so we had
to do some extra work to parse them ourselves, but now that they are
tokenized the appropriate hacking rules to use the new
tokenized text.

Also update all doctests and HACKING.rst to add space after '#' in
'# TODO'.

Note: the hacking code changes won't work with pep8 1.4.6, so the code
and dependency are both changed at the same time.

Change-Id: Ib35d493309fe7e87112a94c74beb70054ca0655c

commit_message:
Neutron Nova Interactions Support

Configure Notification System Options as part of a new class:
neutron::server::notifications.

This class is part of neutron::server because the notifications are sent
by Neutron API service which is configured in neutron-server nodes.

Also add a new type/provider to translate the nova admin tenant to an ID
and set it in neutron.conf.

Closes-bug #1306694
Change-Id: I94334e92bc0057665a281763a4543b127fde7f72
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Add benchmark for tempest. Part 1

This patch provides bases for tempest benchmarking:

1) Modified rally verification for launching tempest scenarios from benchmark
- moved to usage subunit as a test launcher;
- changed access to several methods;
- changed logging.

2) Added TempestContext, which checks tempest installation, initialization
of testrepository and existence of configuration file for tempest.
Also provides launcher for cleanup cloud after benchmarking.

3) Validator for tempest scenario names.

4) TempestScenario with launcher for single tempest test.

bp benchmark-scenarios-based-on-tempest

Change-Id: If67970a49674750b88d27e77c06d89b4e54d5337

commit_message:
Clear barchart before rendering it

When refreshing the bar chart, it is necessary to clear the html
before rendering it. Otherwise the old chart remains on the page,
and the new one is added on top of it. This patch ensures that
the old chart is cleared first, before rendering the new chart.

This also replaces occurrences of .html('') with .empty(),
as the latter is more efficient and explicit.

Closes-bug: #1307563
Change-Id: I5705cb82093dcf45b5111f5ab52d3dfda74ce64a

commit_message:
Add `command_timeout` to shotgun

In case of something wrong with SSH connection (see attached bug for
example), we have to restrict our command execution time, to prevent
hanging of script execution.

Change-Id: Idc21f5320e6259fb703a2814ab0f074ba9ec5b03
Closes-Bug: #1308073

commit_message:
Fixed validation of novanetwork w/o autoassignment

 Novanetwork can't work with floating ip pools with IDs. And it always
 fails to start cluster when novanetwork used without auto_assignment
 of floating IPs. So added feature to check floating ip pools by name
 in validation

Change-Id: I9ef9897a95350e142bd0729402a8f26906349ee5
Closes-Bug: #1308541

commit_message:
Modify the get console API

Changed the return value of the console GET api from string to
the following JSON object:
{'console_enabled': True, 'console_info': {'type': 'shellinaboxd',
   'url': 'http://<hostname>:<port>'}} for the node with console
enabled.
{'console_enabled': False, 'console_info': None} for the node
with console disabled.

Closes-Bug: 1307555

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-04-16 13:43:34.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/vmwareapi/vmops.py', 'nova/virt/vmwareapi/vmware_images.py'], 'message': 'VMware:Avoid transfer overhead for a given image

On concurrent spawn operations, the VMware driver transfers the same
image into different temporary directories before getting into the
cache: the same bits might be downloaded 20 times if 20 spawn
operations happen at the same time for a given image
(before being cached).

The patch addresses this by using locks, enabling only 4 concurrent transfers
(configurable) at a time across clusters per vcenter.

Closes-Bug: #1283325

Change-Id: I21b97f8ee0b961006575f74fef7947b5a5a21b54
'}]
commit_message:
VMware:Avoid transfer overhead for a given image

On concurrent spawn operations, the VMware driver transfers the same
image into different temporary directories before getting into the
cache: the same bits might be downloaded 20 times if 20 spawn
operations happen at the same time for a given image
(before being cached).

The patch addresses this by using locks, enabling only 4 concurrent transfers
(configurable) at a time across clusters per vcenter.

Closes-Bug: #1283325

Change-Id: I21b97f8ee0b961006575f74fef7947b5a5a21b54
