commit_message:
Remove ceilometer.conf.sample

The check-uptodate.sh was removed from the tox checks and therefore
ceilometer.conf.sample is not tested any more to be up to date. As this
sample configuration file changes independently from the project, this check
failed on the gate time to time, as this file  needed to be updated manually.
In order to avoid the need of this periodic manual process, the sample file
is removed from git in this patch and an alternate solution is added for
generating the file manually. Also a README file is added to the place of the
config sample to document this change.

Change-Id: I0bbec0e86f63e6fcd691d626473ed8498024f7ab

commit_message:
Return to using network_api directly for migrations

Previously, we added indirection APIs in conductor to wrap network
methods that still had direct-to-database calls that compute
manager couldn't make. Now that those are cleaned up, we can
remove the use of the indirection layer (and the layer itself from
conductor) and go direct to network_api again.

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

Change-Id: Ia76552f49adf9b0d0128f08e3f99953560d8aa64

subject: fix DELETE request for versioned object
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-04-21 08:40:40.000000000', 'files': ['test/unit/proxy/controllers/test_obj.py', 'swift/proxy/controllers/obj.py'], 'message': "fix DELETE request for versioned object

When using both object versioning and object expiry,
some correct DELETE object requests could fail with
412 precondition failed.

When requsting DELETE object to a versioned container,
current swift always tries to restore a newest versioned
object from a container defined by 'X-Versions-Location'.

However, when the container shows the newest object existing
and acutually it has been expired (i.e. object-expirer has
not swept the actual object yet), such a DELETE request above
always fails until object-expirer delete the object
from the container.

This patch enables to delete such a expired object at
that time of user's DELETE request for a versioned
object and to restore the newest 'available' versioned object.

Closes-Bug: #1308446

Change-Id: I9e3122d2061ded537b08437ac0989043277a6646
"}]
commit_message:
fix DELETE request for versioned object

When using both object versioning and object expiry,
some correct DELETE object requests could fail with
412 precondition failed.

When requsting DELETE object to a versioned container,
current swift always tries to restore a newest versioned
object from a container defined by 'X-Versions-Location'.

However, when the container shows the newest object existing
and acutually it has been expired (i.e. object-expirer has
not swept the actual object yet), such a DELETE request above
always fails until object-expirer delete the object
from the container.

This patch enables to delete such a expired object at
that time of user's DELETE request for a versioned
object and to restore the newest 'available' versioned object.

Closes-Bug: #1308446

Change-Id: I9e3122d2061ded537b08437ac0989043277a6646

commit_message:
Serialize `last_controller` safely

Don't rises exception when a user tries to get default deployment recipe
for a cluster without controllers. Just send him next line

    "last_controller": null

with response.

Closes-Bug: #1296861

subject: Remove secgrp ports from datastore configs
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-04-11 19:53:21.000000000', 'files': ['trove/common/cfg.py', 'trove/taskmanager/models.py', 'trove/extensions/security_group/service.py', 'trove/tests/unittests/taskmanager/test_models.py'], 'message': "Remove secgrp ports from datastore configs

The TCP and UDP ports that are used in security groups configuration
were moved into the datastores configs because it was thought that
they were necessary in the guest. The task manager takes care of
all interaction with nova's security group lifecycle mgmt, and
therfore the values should reside in the task manager config. In
the future, when the user can specify a custom port and/or range
of ports, the guest will be informed of these ports either in the
prepare call, or via the initial configuration itself. There is
no reason these should be in the guest configuration. This further
helps to separate the configuration into what the guest actually
needs versus what appears cleaner, but causes an unclear separation.

partially implements: blueprint refactoring-datastore-options-in-cfg

Change-Id: Ief6ad5629b3462fed98e94c0e2f79c61722e619e
"}]
commit_message:
Remove secgrp ports from datastore configs

The TCP and UDP ports that are used in security groups configuration
were moved into the datastores configs because it was thought that
they were necessary in the guest. The task manager takes care of
all interaction with nova's security group lifecycle mgmt, and
therfore the values should reside in the task manager config. In
the future, when the user can specify a custom port and/or range
of ports, the guest will be informed of these ports either in the
prepare call, or via the initial configuration itself. There is
no reason these should be in the guest configuration. This further
helps to separate the configuration into what the guest actually
needs versus what appears cleaner, but causes an unclear separation.

partially implements: blueprint refactoring-datastore-options-in-cfg

Change-Id: Ief6ad5629b3462fed98e94c0e2f79c61722e619e

commit_message:

commit_message:
WIP: dvr_flow_pulling_channel

Add pulling channel between ovs agent and ML2 plugin, to support dvr flow
population. The pulling operation is triggered in ovs loop. Everytime port
changes happen, after regular flow processing, agent pulls dvr info from
plugin side for those port changes, and populates corresponding flows into
local ovs.

Change-Id: If0912059ba4582aabe7e48389cc774c70afe40a4

commit_message:
Local hacking rule to restrict migration imports

We want to be careful about what we import in a sqlalchemy migration
file, so add a whitelist what is allowed and enforce via a local hacking
rule.

In order for this to work - it requires
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/80018/ to be in a hacking release used
by Nova.

Change-Id: I4d8655f7c3de35c9e5c172f706a3f0418093c8bb

commit_message:
Allow passing a req.Session object to old client

requests.Session management is expected to be handled by the new
keystoneclient.session object however there is some need for people
using the existing client pattern to pass their own requests.Session.
This simply passes the option through to the keystoneclient.Session
builder if a requests.Session is provided.

DocImpact: new requests_session parameter on keystoneclient.HTTPClient.
           This means it is available on v2 and v3 clients as well.
Change-Id: I985245f433418ec72ec5ad5a316b33fb6d3d4117
Partial-Bug: #1282089

commit_message:
Adds the new IBM SDN-VE plugin

It adds a new plugin for SDN-VE, the IBM SDN
controller. The plugin supports the core API
and the port binding and L3 extensions.

Implements: blueprint ibm-sdn-ve-plugin
DocImpact

Change-Id: I92619a95bca2ae0c37e7fdd39da30119b43d1ad6

commit_message:
The sdnve controller ips should be parsed and converted into list.

After read from the configuration file, the ips config options contains
the ip addresses of sdnve controllers in string format. However, the
following usage should take it as a list.

Fix Bug1310455.

Change-Id: Iaf9f8d02e07afd52c8a59a9444b6deb27d9a2c20

The interfaces templates for /etc/network/interfaces contain 2 gateway
definitions, and there is a third one configured via DHCP when the

'}]
commit_message:
Remove gateway definitions in interfaces

The interfaces templates for /etc/network/interfaces contain 2 gateway
definitions, and there is a third one configured via DHCP when the
network comes up.

Having multiple default gateways (at least configured this way) does
not work. For instance, booting into Ubuntu 12.04.4 LTS with one of
these interface definitions results in error messages ("Waiting up to
60 more seconds for network configuration", "Booting system without
full network configuration").

With the gateways removed, the network comes up without a problem and
the hosts can communicate over the API Network, the OpenStack Management
Network, and the Data Network. (And there is still a default gateway
on the NAT interfaces of each host).

Change-Id: I3ee9737c19b696d88f9897547996cddef482b7f7

commit_message:
Fix mac address and task_state in baremetal-node-list

Currently nova baremetal-node-list doesn't display the
list of MAC addresses for each node because this is part
of the interfaces object, and not a top level field.

It also doesn't display the task state, which is very useful
when trying to find which nodes have failed to build.

This change fixes both issues

Change-Id: If7a3bcab1220be400519ac811bd727ca8ff85827
Closes-Bug: #1308147
